.TH "WEBTRANSPORTSENDSTREAM.GETSTATS" "3JS" "February 24, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebTransportSendStream.getStats \- WebTransportSendStream: getStats()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]getStats()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]WebTransportSendStream\f[R] interface asynchronously returns an
object containing statistics for the current stream.
.PP
The statistics include the total number of bytes written to the stream,
the number that have been sent (ignoring packet overhead), and the
number of bytes that have been set at least once, and the number that
have been acknowledged (up until the first sequentially\-ordered
non\-acknowledged byte).
It therefore provides a measure of how quickly the application is
sending bytes to the server on this particular stream.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getStats()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that resolves to an object containing statistics
about the current stream.
The returned object has the following properties:
.TP
\f[B]bytesAcknowledged\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of bytes written to this stream
that have been sent and acknowledged as received by the server, using
QUIC\(cqs ACK mechanism.
Only sequential bytes up to, but not including, the first
non\-acknowledged byte, are counted.
This number can only increase and is always less than or equal to
\f[CR]bytesSent\f[R].
When the connection is over HTTP/2, the value will match
\f[CR]bytesSent\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]bytesSent\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of bytes written to this stream
that have been sent at least once (but not necessarily acknowledged).
This number can only increase, and is always less than or equal to
\f[CR]bytesWritten\f[R].
Note that this count does not include bytes sent as network overhead
(such as packet headers).
.TP
\f[B]bytesWritten\f[R]
A positive integer indicating the number of bytes successfully written
to this stream.
This number can only increase.
.SH EXAMPLES
The code snippet below uses \f[CR]await\f[R] to wait on the
\f[CR]Promise\f[R] returned by \f[CR]getStats()\f[R].
When the promise fulfills, the result for the number of bytes that have
been sent but not acknowledged is logged to the console.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] stats = \f[B]await\f[R] stream.getStats();
\f[B]const\f[R] bytesNotReceived = stats.bytesWritten \- stats.bytesAcknowledged;
console.log(\(gaBytes still successfully sent: ${bytesNotReceived}\(ga);
.EE
